---
title: Plant-Based Gouda Beyond Burger™ Made for Meat Lovers; Made from Plants
description: There are a lot of burger recipes out there, we know. Believe us when we say: this one truly goes above and beyond! Delicious Beyond Burger plant-based patties are topped with melty gouda cheese, jammy balsamic onions, tangy ketchup, and a creamy, Dijon-spiked aioli. Yeah, these bodacious burgers are sure to satisfy meat lovers and vegetarians alike (hello, 20g of plant protein!). Oh, and all of this goodness comes with crispy potato wedges and pickle spears on the side. That’s a lot to love.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5e25fed72ae33135333fad5e-e69e1d4c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/plant-based-goudalicious-beyond-burger-5e25fed72ae33135333fad5e-6beec996.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 1020 kcal
  fat: 56 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 100 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 2340 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/plant-based-goudalicious-beyond-burger-5e25fed72ae33135333fad5e
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Quarter @dill pickle{1}(quartered lengthwise).

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounces} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a
#baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half
the @fry seasoning{2%tablespoons} (you'll use the rest later). Roast on top
rack, flipping halfway through, until golden brown and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add onion and
cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.
> TIP: If onion begins to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoons} and @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4
servings). Continue cooking until caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more.
Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash
out pan.

Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove} (2 cloves for 4 servings). In a second small
bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoons}, @sour cream{2%tablespoons},
@Dijon mustard{2%teaspoons}, and minced garlic to taste. Season with salt and
pepper. Halve @brioche buns{2}; toast until golden.

Season @Beyond Burgers{8%ounces} patties all over with salt, pepper, and
remaining fry seasoning. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in pan
used for onion over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned,
~{3-5%minutes} per side.
> TIP: Lower heat if seasoning begins to burn.

Top each patty with @gouda cheese{2%slices}. Reduce heat to medium; cover pan
until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Spread bottom buns with half the @ketchup{4%tablespoons} and top buns with a
thin layer of aioli. Fill buns with patties and as much onion jam as you like.
Serve with potato wedges, pickle spears, and remaining aioli and ketchup on the
side.